File: Metrobus has apologised to commuters for the inconvenience. JOHANNESBURG - The City of Johannesburg has suspended its Metrobus services for a second day. The halt in service is because of a strike by the Democratic Municipal And Allied Workers Union. READ: Metrobus reduces service due to petrol strike Demawusa is demanding higher salaries for experienced employees. Metrobus has apologised to commuters for the inconvenience. A meeting between the company and workers is scheduled for Tuesday